sDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528384\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528384\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 22, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hvd1665702670692.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hvd1665702670692.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hvd1665702670692.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hvd1665702670692\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specifies one or more logical printers for the application. Windows only.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__section_lxy_xhq_xvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d355611e50\">Syntax</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">LogPrinter</span> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>} <code class=\"ph codeph\">PRT_</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">LogicalPrinterName</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__section_gcc_13q_xvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d355611e71\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__table_w3249ab1b5b3b3_w3250ab1b5b3_w3251ab1b5_w3252ab1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">usys.ini</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[printer]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">None</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__section_fxl_d3q_xvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d355611e117\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">A logical printer is a named collection of printer settings for a physical printer. You can\n        define more than one logical printer to be mapped to the same physical printer. However, you\n        cannot define multiple logical printers with the same name. To define logical printers, the\n        Setup utility must be enabled for your application. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kko1705481411881.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kko1705481411881.html\" title=\"The Setup Utility enables users to change selected initialization settings in usys.ini without restarting the application. It can be added to the system menu of an MDI Uniface desktop application.\">Setup Utility</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qdk1665702675095.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qdk1665702675095.html\" title=\"On Windows, you can define a logical printer, which is a named collection of printer settings for a physical printer. You can define more than one logical printer for the same physical printer.\">Define a Logical Printer</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__p_d145673e1_d145674e1_d145675e1\">The logical printer definitions are stored in the\n        Windows Registry. For each logical printer, an entry is added to the\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">LogPrinter</span> setting in <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__p_d145676e1_d145677e1_d145678e1\">For example, if you defined a logical printer called\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">DEF_LANDSCAPE</code>, an entry called <code class=\"ph codeph\">PRT_DEF_LANDSCAPE</code> is\n        added to <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">LogPrinter</span>:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__pre_kjq_g3q_xvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[printer]\nlogprinter=PRT_DEF_PORTRAIT, PRT_DEF_LANDSCAPE</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__section_n3q_33q_xvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d355611e167\">Search Path for Logical Printers</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__p_d145682e1_d145683e1_d145684e1\">When Uniface looks for logical printer definitions, it\n        looks for logical printers under the following Registry keys in the specified order:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__ol_sfp_q3q_xvb\">\n<li class=\"li\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Uniface/Uniface\n              <var class=\"keyword varname\">Version</var>/<var class=\"keyword varname\">ApsName</var></code></li>\n<li class=\"li\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Uniface/Uniface\n          <var class=\"keyword varname\">Version</var>/</code></li>\n<li class=\"li\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Uniface/<var class=\"keyword varname\">UnifaceAdmDir</var>/<var class=\"keyword varname\">IniFileName</var></code></li>\n<li class=\"li\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Uniface/<var class=\"keyword varname\">UnifaceAdmDir</var>/<var class=\"keyword varname\">IniFileName</var></code></li>\n<li class=\"li\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Uniface/<var class=\"keyword varname\">UnifaceAdmDir</var>/default_ini</code></li>\n</ol>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__ul_pxy_y3q_xvb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__li_d50708e1_d50709e1_d50710e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Version</var> is the main version number, such as <code class=\"ph codeph\">9</code> or\n            <code class=\"ph codeph\">10</code>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__li_d50711e1_d50712e1_d50713e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ApsName</var> is the name of the application shell. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__li_d50714e1_d50715e1_d50716e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">UnifaceAdmDir</var> is the directory specified by the USYSADM path logical. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__li_d50717e1_d50718e1_d50719e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">IniFileName</var> is the name of an initialization file. If not specified,\n            <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span> is assumed. </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\">On Windows, Uniface always writes logical printer definitions to the second location. For\n        logical printer definitions to be moved or copied to any other location, you must use\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$setting</span>.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__note_blt_cjq_xvb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Due to Microsoft restrictions, Uniface writes to locations under\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">HKEY_CURRENT_USER</code>. To write to locations under\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE</code>, you must run Uniface as administrator and disable\n        Registry Virtualization before using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$setting</span>. For more information,\n        refer to <a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us%2Flibrary%2Fwindows%2Fdesktop%2Faa965884%28v%3Dvs.85%29.aspx\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Registry Virtualization</a> on MSDN.</div>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"hvd1665702670692__note_izm_ljq_xvb\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> Making changes to the Registry can significantly\n        affect your computer, so use due care when using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$setting</span>. Uniface cannot\n        be held responsible for changes you make to your Registry.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qdk1665702675095.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define a Logical Printer</a><p>On Windows, you can define a logical printer, which is a named collection of printer settings for a physical printer. You can define more than one logical printer for the same physical printer.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528384\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528384\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "LogPrinter Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 22, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Specifies one or more logical printers for the application. Windows only. Syntax LogPrinter { = } PRT_ LogicalPrinterName Defaults Assignment file usys.ini Section [printer] Default value None Description A logical printer is a named collection of printer settings for a physical printer. You can define more than one logical printer to be mapped to the same physical printer. However, you cannot define multiple logical printers with the same name. To define logical printers, the Setup utility must be enabled for your application. For more information, see Setup Utility and Define a Logical Printer . The logical printer definitions are stored in the Windows Registry. For each logical printer, an entry is added to the LogPrinter setting in usys.ini . For example, if you defined a logical printer called DEF_LANDSCAPE , an entry called PRT_DEF_LANDSCAPE is added to LogPrinter : [printer] logprinter=PRT_DEF_PORTRAIT, PRT_DEF_LANDSCAPE Copy Search Path for Logical Printers When Uniface looks for logical printer definitions, it looks for logical printers under the following Registry keys in the specified order: HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Uniface/Uniface Version / ApsName HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Uniface/Uniface Version / HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Uniface/ UnifaceAdmDir / IniFileName HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Uniface/ UnifaceAdmDir / IniFileName HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Uniface/ UnifaceAdmDir /default_ini Version is the main version number, such as 9 or 10 . ApsName is the name of the application shell. UnifaceAdmDir is the directory specified by the USYSADM path logical. IniFileName is the name of an initialization file. If not specified, usys.ini is assumed. On Windows, Uniface always writes logical printer definitions to the second location. For logical printer definitions to be moved or copied to any other location, you must use $setting . Note: Due to Microsoft restrictions, Uniface writes to locations under HKEY_CURRENT_USER . To write to locations under HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE , you must run Uniface as administrator and disable Registry Virtualization before using $setting . For more information, refer to Registry Virtualization on MSDN. CAUTION: Making changes to the Registry can significantly affect your computer, so use due care when using $setting . Uniface cannot be held responsible for changes you make to your Registry. Related Links Define a Logical Printer On Windows, you can define a logical printer, which is a named collection of printer settings for a physical printer. You can define more than one logical printer for the same physical printer. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}